FBIS4-33986 "drlat114aa_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-114 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Panamanian Minister Opposes Sanctions Panamanian Minister Opposes Sanctions PA1306203794 Panama City Telemetro Television Network in Spanish 1730 GMT 13 Jun 94 PA1306203794 Panama City Telemetro Television Network Spanish BFN [From the "Telemetro Reports" newscast] [Text] Foreign Minister Jose Raul Mulino has stated that the application of economic sanctions and the trade embargo decreed against Haiti will harm the Haitian people more than their leaders. Mulino made this statement during his visit to Colombia, where the Fourth Ibero-American Summit begins tomorrow. According to the Panamanian foreign minister, the Haitian case is similar to the U.S. blockade against Cuba.
